      "title": "Model files",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Files (auto-downloadable via the manager links):\n- krea2_turbo_fp8_scaled (or krea2_raw_bf16 - see GENERATE note)\n- qwen3vl_4b_fp8_scaled text encoder, type 'krea2'\n- qwen_image_vae\n- krea2_identity_edit_v1_2.safetensors LoRA (this model)"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 101,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        640,
        330
      ],
      "size": [
        520,
        190
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 7,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "How inputs work",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "YOUR IMAGE - the image being edited (your character, the photo to\nrestyle, the scene...).\n\nTwo-image mode (group 2 enabled): THIS slot is always the SCENE\n(image 1). The person always goes in group 2 (image 2).\nInputs around 1MP work best. Two-person images: stay at/below ~1.5MP."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 102,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        640,
        1130
      ],
      "size": [
        520,
        210
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 8,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Enable for two-image edits",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "OPTIONAL second reference - the PERSON for insert-into-scene edits\n('place this person at the table').\n\nThis group ships DISABLED (purple = bypassed) - the workflow is a\nplain single-image editor until you need it.\nEnable: right-click this group's title bar -> toggle Bypass off.\nOrder rule: scene = image 1 (group 1), person = image 2 (here)."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 103,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        1620,
        360
      ],
      "size": [
        620,
        300
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 9,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Writing instructions",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Write the edit in plain English:\n  'Relight the scene with warm golden hour sunlight.'\n  'Place this person at the cafe table, holding a coffee.'\n  'Change her outfit to a red raincoat.'\n\nUnique face coming out generic? Append:\n  'Preserve the exact facial identity - distinguishing features: ...'\nand describe what makes the face distinctive.\n\ngrounding_px: how large the model 'sees' the input while reading your\ninstruction. 384-768 is the trained range. Getting doubled/split\ncompositions? LOWER it. The collapsed node below is the negative -\nonly used at CFG > 1; keep its prompt empty."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 104,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        2320,
        230
      ],
      "size": [
        420,
        420
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 10,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Fidelity dial",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "THE FIDELITY DIAL (ref_boost) - how hard the model looks at your\nreference. New in this release.\n\n  1.0 = classic v1.1 behavior\n  4.0 = recommended (pre-set): much stronger face + body likeness,\n        more reliable edits\n  >10 = over-copy: removals/replacements start failing\n  <1  = suppress the reference (creative freedom)\n\nref_boost_a: the scene dial (image 1) in two-image mode -\nleave at 1.0 unless you are exploring. ref_boost applies to the\nperson (image 2) when group 2 is enabled, else to your image.\n\nfit_mode: how inputs fit a different output aspect\nratio. fit = resample to the output shape (default, recommended); crop (legacy) = center-crop\nonly for v1/v1.1 weights."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        2800,
        490
      ],
      "size": [
        320,
        280
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 11,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "Sampling",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Turbo model: 10 steps, cfg 1.\n\nStep dial:\n  8  = stronger composition/instruction adherence\n  12 = more face detail\n  10 = balanced\n\nUsing krea2_raw instead of turbo:\n40 steps, cfg 3-4 (negative then matters)."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 106,
      "type": "Note",
      "pos": [
        620,
        -600
      ],
      "size": [
        1600,
        330
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 12,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "README",
      "properties": {
        "Node name for S&R": "Note"
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "KREA 2 IDENTITY EDIT  -  v1.2 (Fidelity update)\nUse an image like a LoRA: your character/scene goes in as a reference, plain-English\ninstructions do the rest.\n\nQUICK START:  1) load your image in group 1   2) write the instruction in group 3   3) Queue.\nThe Fidelity dial (group 4) ships at 4 = strong likeness. Two-image person-into-scene: enable\ngroup 2 (right-click its title -> toggle Bypass).\n\nRequires the comfyui-krea2edit nodes from this release or newer.\ngithub.com/lbouaraba/comfyui-krea2edit   -   huggingface.co/conradlocke/krea2-identity-edit"
      ],
      "color": "#232",
      "bgcolor": "#353"
    },
